          <div class="card-body events text-center">
            <h5 class="card-title events">TV MINISTRY</h5>
            <p class="card-text events text-left">
              Pastor Tony Freitas uses the Local TV Station, Youtube, Facebook and Website to Preach the Word of God to the ones that he cannot reach in person.<br> 
              Media is the vehicle for communication for God’s message to man. And there is no better place to examine media than the Bible because it contains a history of the communication between God and Man as well as the various methods (Medias “Ways”) used to accomplish it. God reveal Himself to Adam and Eve, prophets, Apostles in person and He also used other effective methods that were suitable for the time and person in question for example:<br> 
Face to face with Adam and Eve: Genesis 3:8<br>
In the form of an angel for Abraham: Genesis 18:1-3<br>
In dreams and visions for Joseph : Genesis 37:5<br>
With a burning bush for Moses: Exodus 3:1-9<br>
The sound of a voice and the appearance of a dove for the witnesses of Jesus' baptism: Matthew 3:13-17<br>
Tongues of fire for the Apostles: Acts 2:3-4<br>
It’s does not matter how you get the true word of God - All it matters is that you listen to it.<br> 
If you can attend in person to any of our worship services, we urge to do so. Let’s Praise the Lord Together.<br>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card events">
          <img class="card-img-top" src="/images/joyous_hands.webp" alt="Worship Services">
          <div class="card-body events text-center">
            <h5 class="card-title events">Worship Services</h5>
            <p class="card-text text-left">
              Each week we must all Worship Together. Worshiping Jesus together may be the single most important thing we do. Every Christian is a member of the universal church because by definition Christians are believers in Christ. They are members of His body. It is important to find a good (Biblical) church.  It is not until we are able to rightly prioritize God above everything else in our world that we can begin to worship in spirit and truth.<br>
              <br>
              <b>Romans 12:5</b><br>
              <i>... so in Christ we who are many form one body, and each member belongs to all the others.</i> (NIV)<br>
              <br>
              It is for our own good that God want us in fellowship with other believers. We need each other to grow up in the faith, to learn to serve, to love one another, to exercise our spiritual gifts, and to practice forgiveness.<br>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="card events">
          <img class="card-img-top" src="/images/funeral_flowers.jpg" alt="Funeral Services">
          <div class="card-body events">
            <h5 class="card-title events text-center">Funeral Services</h5>
            <p class="card-text events text-left">
            THE TRANSFORMATION OF LIFE WITH A CARING PASTOR<br>
            <br>
            Don’t desert the one who is dying, advises Pastor Tony Freitas of A & Z God's Ministry for All People. The person who is dying usually knows that he or she is dying, and the secret for us is not to be afraid of that or to run away from it. Ask them what they’re thinking about, what they may need. Often, our emotions mirror those of the person with whom we are talking. In those moments, one wounded heart reaches out to another, and they connect. That can be a beautiful experience, Just holding hands and praying.<br>
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

